    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine and a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example is mechanically sound, featuring a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal (RMS). The naturally aspirated powerplant delivers linear torque through the rev range, complemented by a precise short-throw shifter. The chassis retains its factory-spec handling characteristics with a McPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing plenty of pad life. The exterior displays minor road-rash consistent with its mileage, but the underbody is clean and free of significant corrosion. Recent maintenance includes a high-performance brake fluid flush and a fresh set of N-rated Michelin Pilot Sport tires.",
